# Core Workflow

You are working on the enhanced-relay gateway (refactor of new-api). Read
`AGENTS.md` and `docs/` before non-trivial work. Never bypass the acceptance gate.

## The loop (TDD, red first)

1. Pick/confirm the requirement ID (`REQ-...`) in `acceptance/requirements.json`.
   New behavior needs a new ID there.
2. Write a **failing** test that binds the ID: `req.Covers(t, "REQ-...")`.
3. Implement until green.
4. Run the gate and make it pass (see below).

## Definition of Done (all machine-checked — do not self-certify)

- `make verify-fast` passes locally; `make ci-docker` passes before you claim done
  (race + traceability + mutation). On Windows use Docker/WSL — never skip race.
- Every P0/P1 requirement has a passing bound test (dashboard shows 0 unmet).
- Core packages meet the mutation threshold (`MUTATION_THRESHOLD`, currently 80%).
- No new `t.Skip`, no weakened assertions, no edited `*.golden` without a reason.

## Hard rules

- Do NOT weaken or delete tests/assertions to go green. Fix the code.
- Do NOT commit unless explicitly asked.
- If a gate fails and you cannot fix it, STOP and report — never disable the gate.
- View results at `build/dashboard.html` (open in a browser); evidence JSON in `build/`.
